properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 9 at 4:42AM AKST until January 11 at 12:00AM AKST by NWS Juneau AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...The Taku winds. Northeast winds 30 mph with gusts up to
80 mph expected.

* WHERE...Douglas, Downtown Juneau, West Juneau, and Thane.

* WHEN...From 6 PM this evening to midnight AKST Friday night.

* TIMING...Gusty winds will rise today with gusts reaching 60 mph
by early this evening. Peak gusts will occur Friday morning and
Friday afternoon when gusts will be around 80 mph before easing
Friday evening.

* IMPACTS....Objects will be blown around in the wind. Blowing
snow could cause low visibility at times. Power outages are
possible. Travel will be difficult, especially for high profile
vehicles.
properties.instruction:
People should prepare for possible power outages. Use caution if
you must drive.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 6 PM THIS EVENING TO MIDNIGHT AKST FRIDAY NIGHT
